 <!-- 
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
    Schema: Assembly_feature_relationship_arm  Entity: Constrained_kinematic_motion_representation
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
   -->
    <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Constrained_kinematic_motion_representation">
 A <b>Constrained_kinematic_motion_representation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Geometric_relationship_with_placement_transformation"/> that represents a kinematic motion constrained by a
kinematic pair between a pair of assembly features. The relationship is represented as a relative
kinematics motion between a pair of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/> instances belonging to two
<express_ref linkend="assembly_feature_relationship:arm:Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Representative_geometric_model"/> instances which represent target assembly features. 
 
 
 
<note>Detailed
information about the constraints is derived by applying the entity <express_ref linkend="kinematic_structure_schema:ir_express:kinematic_structure_schema.kinematic_pair"/> defined in ISO
10303-105. </note>
<note>When mapped to the corresponding MIM object there are additional constraints to ensure that the items defining the transformation are properly related and that the transformation operator is a <express_ref linkend="kinematic_structure_schema:ir_express:kinematic_structure_schema.kinematic_pair"/>. </note>
 
  
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: assembly_feature_relationship_arm  Entity: Constrained_kinematic_motion_representation Attribute: rep_1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Constrained_kinematic_motion_representation.rep_1">
an instance of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/> of the type
<express_ref linkend="assembly_feature_relationship:arm:Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Representative_geometric_model"/> to which the transformation applies. 
 </ext_description>
 
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: assembly_feature_relationship_arm  Entity: Constrained_kinematic_motion_representation Attribute: rep_2
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Constrained_kinematic_motion_representation.rep_2">
an instance of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/> of the type
<express_ref linkend="assembly_feature_relationship:arm:Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Representative_geometric_model"/> which is related to <b>rep_2</b> by the transformation.

</ext_description>



<!-- WR1 -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Constrained_kinematic_motion_representation.wr:WR1">
   Both the source and the target of the transformation shall be of type <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_3d"/>.
 </ext_description>



<!-- 
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
    Schema: Assembly_feature_relationship_arm  Entity: Free_kinematic_motion_representation
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
   -->
    <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Free_kinematic_motion_representation">
 A <b>Free_kinematic_motion_representation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Geometric_model_relationship_with_transformation"/> that represents the free kinematic motion in three dimensional
space of an assembly feature with respect to another assembly feature. 
 
 
 
<note>Detailed
information about the constraints is derived by applying the entity <express_ref linkend="kinematic_structure_schema:ir_express:kinematic_structure_schema.kinematic_pair"/> defined in ISO
10303-105. </note>
<note>When mapped to the corresponding MIM object there are additional constraints to ensure that the items defining the transformation are properly related and that the transformation operator is a <express_ref linkend="kinematic_structure_schema:ir_express:kinematic_structure_schema.kinematic_pair"/>. </note>
 
  
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: assembly_feature_relationship_arm  Entity: Free_kinematic_motion_representation Attribute: rep_1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Free_kinematic_motion_representation.rep_1">
an instance of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/> of the type
<express_ref linkend="assembly_feature_relationship:arm:Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Representative_geometric_model"/> to which the transformation applies. 
 </ext_description>
 
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: assembly_feature_relationship_arm  Entity: Free_kinematic_motion_representation Attribute: rep_2
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Free_kinematic_motion_representation.rep_2">
an instance of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/> of the type
<express_ref linkend="assembly_feature_relationship:arm:Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Representative_geometric_model"/> which is related to <b>rep_1</b> by the transformation.

</ext_description>


<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: assembly_feature_relationship_arm  Entity: Free_kinematic_motion_representation Attribute: motion
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Free_kinematic_motion_representation.motion">
a description of the free kinematic motion. The motion is described by the transformation
between two instances of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/> belonging to two different instances of
<express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/>.

</ext_description>






 
 <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: assembly_feature_relationship_arm  Entity: Representative_geometric_model
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Representative_geometric_model">
	 A <b>Representative_geometric_model</b> is a  type of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/>
that is a representative shape of a product definition or a shape aspect.
 
  <note>A representative shape is a <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/> that represents the referenced product definition or
shape element with the most detailed geometric representation. Identification of the most detailed geometric representation becomes necessary as this module represents the geometric information of connectivity between constituents at the most detailed geometric level, and as one product definition
or one shape element may be represented by two or more <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model"/>s.</note> 
 
 <note> The corresponding MIM object has an additional constaint, validated by special purpose functions, that requires the  <b>Representative_geometric_model</b> to be unique for any related  product definion or shape element.</note>
 
 </ext_description>




 <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: assembly_feature_relationship_arm  Entity: Shape_element_relationship_representation_association 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Shape_element_relationship_representation_association">
 A <b>Shape_element_relationship_representation_association</b> is an association that identifies an instance of <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_
relationship"/> representing the geometric information of an instance of <express_ref linkend="shape_property_assignment:arm:Shape_property_assignment_arm.Shape_element_relationship"/>.
This entity is used to describe the relative position and orientation between a pair of <express_ref linkend="shape_property_assignment:arm:Shape_property_assignment_arm.Shape_element"/> 
instances.  
	 
	
   </ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: assembly_feature_relationship_arm  Entity: Shape_element_relationship_representation_association Attribute: represented_shape_elmement_relationship
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Shape_element_relationship_representation_association.represented_shape_element_relationship">
a pair of <express_ref linkend="shape_property_assignment:arm:Shape_property_assignment_arm.Shape_element"/> instances whose geometric relationship is represented by the <express_ref linkend="assembly_feature_relationship:arm:Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Shape_element_relationship_representation_association.representing_representation_relationship"/>.



 </ext_description>
  
 <!-- 
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
    Schema: assembly_feature_relationship_arm  Entity: Shape_element_relationship_representation_association Attribute: representing_representation_relationship
   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
   -->
    <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Shape_element_relationship_representation_association.representing_representation_relationship">
 an instance of <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_relationship"/> that
 represents the geometric information of the <express_ref linkend="assembly_feature_relationship:arm:Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Shape_element_relationship_representation_association.represented_shape_element_relationship"/>.
 </ext_description>
   
 <!-- WR1 -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Shape_element_relationship_representation_association.wr:WR1">
   The <b>representing_representation_relationship</b> shall be a relationship between a pair of
<express_ref linkend="assembly_feature_relationship:arm:Assembly_feature_relationship_arm.Representative_geometric_model"/> instances.
 </ext_description>


